"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-01-fans-go-crazy-simone-biles-shows-off-brilliant-new-necklace-winning-olympic-gold-21345423\", \"text\": \"Simone Biles continued her Olympic redemption story by claiming her second gymnastics gold in Paris and sixth overall.  Biles helped Team USA pick up gold in a team event earlier this week and continue her impressive form in the individual all-around final on Thursday evening.  The American won this title back at Rio in 2016 and was favourite in Tokyo five years later but pulled out after suffering from the 'twisties'.  Biles produced a sensational display in the Paris event, becoming the oldest winner of her sport's blue-riband event for 72 years.  After beating Brazil's Rebeca Andrade and defending champion Sunisa Lee to gold, Biles showed off a new necklace - a sparkly goat in reference to her tag as the greatest of all time.  'A lot of people love calling me the GOAT, they always do it, so I thought it would be really special if I got one made,' Biles toldEurosportwhen asked about her new piece of jewellery.  'The haters hate it so I love it even more. It's just a special part of me that I have him, as well as a stuffed goat back at the village, just as a reminder to me that I can do this and I have done it before.'  Biles finished with an overall score of 59.131, with Brazil's Rebeca Andrade taking silver and defending champion Sunisa Lee.  'Oh my gosh I am ecstatic with my performances,' Biles told Eurosport. 'It was all pretty good in my opinion, I could not have asked for more.  'I was a little worried about Rebeca, we were neck and neck basically the whole way through and she's a phenomenal gymnast. I am glad she was there to push me.'  Reacting to Biles' latest gold-winning performance, BBC commentator Matt Baker said: 'What a comeback, wow.  'That was absolutely incredible - on so many levels. Simone Biles is back where she belongs. Absolutely another level.  'You can feel the admiration and respect from everyone here - that is the way to do it. Goodness me it wasn't easy, it had its ups-and-downs, but surely that is your champion.'  The GOAT necklace?? Omg! Yes Simone Biles!!#OlympicGames  simone biles wearing a goat necklace is iconic \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0082  SIMONE BILES WEARING A DIMAOND GOAT NECKLACE! YESSSSSSSS. \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0090\\u0090\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0090\\u0090  Simone Biles wearing a goat necklace\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0092\\u00af  SIMONE BILES IS THAT A GOAT NECKLACE  Is that a goat necklace?? \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a4\\u00a3\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a4\\u00a3 I will repeat, SIMONE BILES IS THAT GIRL \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u008f\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u00be  Simone Biles immediately putting on a necklace of a diamond goat is honestly the energy I am absolutely here for. Love her.  Nah sorry Simone Biles putting on her goat necklace after coming 1st and the coach shouting period! We love to see it  Terrifyingly, for her rivals at least, Biles could yet add three more golds to her collection ahead of three individual finals.  She is due to take part in the vault final on Saturday and the beam and floor finals on Monday.  Biles holds the record for most women's all-around world titles and most world championship medals.  Before Paris 2024 she was already the most decorated gymnast with 37 world medals.  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:Olympic tennis ball girl goes viral for giving Novak Djokovic a flirty look  ArrowMORE:Andy Murray heartbroken to miss out on 'fairytale ending' at Paris Olympics  ArrowMORE:Hollywood megastar set to perform death-defying stunt during Olympics closing ceremony  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPriv